# .cursorignore - FULL AI block: no indexing, no Agent/Tab/Inline-Edit access, no @-mention.
# https://cursor.com/docs/reference/ignore-file
#
# Cursor already auto-respects .gitignore, so node_modules/, dist/, caches, and other
# gitignored paths are excluded from indexing WITHOUT being listed here. This file is
# reserved for the narrow case gitignore does not cover: files that must stay in the repo
# (or on disk) but that the model must never read or touch - i.e. secrets/credentials.
#
# Large, generated, or vendored files the agent may still legitimately open on demand
# (lockfile, generated *.d.ts, compiled skill manuals) belong in .cursorindexingignore,
# which removes them from search WITHOUT blocking access.
#
# Note: per the docs this is best-effort due to LLM unpredictability, NOT a hard security
# boundary. Real secrets should stay out of the repo and context entirely where possible.

# Cloudflare local secrets (keep the *.example templates readable)
**/.dev.vars
**/.dev.vars.*
!**/.dev.vars.example
**/.prod.vars
**/.prod.vars.*
**/.staging.vars
**/.staging.vars.*

# Environment files (keep the *.example templates readable)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
!**/.env.production.example

# Private keys & certificates
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/id_rsa
**/id_ed25519
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx

# Generic credential / secret files (mirrors the commit-secret guard regex and Cursor's own
# recommended secret patterns: https://cursor.com/docs/reference/ignore-file)
**/credentials.json
**/secrets.json

# Local agent overrides that may hold tokens or machine-specific paths
**/.claude/settings.local.json
**/.cursor/settings.local.json
CLAUDE.local.md
